WEBVTT

00:00:36.307 --> 00:00:37.475
Hey, Bulgae.

00:00:37.975 --> 00:00:39.143
Now make your choice.

00:00:40.019 --> 00:00:42.521
You can either fight against us

00:00:43.397 --> 00:00:46.192
or join us and fight against them.

00:01:23.145 --> 00:01:24.855
I never imagined this would happen.

00:01:36.784 --> 00:01:38.285
Beom-ryong's strength.

00:01:46.961 --> 00:01:48.295
Mr. Jeong's skills.

00:01:49.296 --> 00:01:50.297
And

00:01:51.132 --> 00:01:52.258
Bulgae's...

00:02:07.022 --> 00:02:08.774
brains?

00:02:19.618 --> 00:02:22.663
Anyway, with a lineup like that,
there's no way we can lose.

00:02:25.124 --> 00:02:26.250
With those three

00:02:28.210 --> 00:02:29.962
we can take on anyone and win.

00:02:32.298 --> 00:02:33.549
Out of breath?

00:02:33.632 --> 00:02:35.259
Getting winded over something like this?

00:02:35.593 --> 00:02:36.802
I guess your skills
have gotten pretty rusty.

00:02:36.886 --> 00:02:40.097
You played dirty, throwing dirt.
You darn rascal.

00:02:41.223 --> 00:02:43.058
Anyway, I finished first.

00:02:43.142 --> 00:02:46.187
Hey, you lie every time
you open your mouth.

00:02:46.437 --> 00:02:48.731
- I was the fastest!
- What are you talking about?

00:02:48.814 --> 00:02:50.483
I finished first
and was waiting, you punk.

00:02:50.566 --> 00:02:51.650
What?

00:02:52.318 --> 00:02:53.527
Jeez.

00:02:53.903 --> 00:02:56.822
Hey, Gong-bok. You saw everything.
Who took them down the fastest?

00:02:59.033 --> 00:03:00.075
Who?

00:03:02.787 --> 00:03:04.038
What are you even doing over there?

00:03:05.664 --> 00:03:06.665
Or maybe not?

00:03:07.291 --> 00:03:08.918
Did I see it wrong?

00:03:18.719 --> 00:03:21.347
You guys look like a bunch of mercenaries.

00:03:21.847 --> 00:03:23.390
Who hired you?

00:03:28.187 --> 00:03:29.355
As if I'm going to tell you.

00:03:30.231 --> 00:03:31.315
Darn it.

00:03:36.111 --> 00:03:38.239
Wait a minute. Don't move!

00:03:42.076 --> 00:03:43.494
I think this is him.

00:03:46.705 --> 00:03:49.625
VIP CUSTOMER: HEAVEN CASINO

00:03:52.086 --> 00:03:53.587
Did you secure the package?

00:03:56.131 --> 00:03:58.384
Why aren't you answering?
The chairman is waiting.

00:03:59.343 --> 00:04:01.011
The chairman, you say.

00:04:01.846 --> 00:04:02.930
Who are you?

00:04:03.013 --> 00:04:04.431
If you went to the trouble
of hiring mercenaries

00:04:04.515 --> 00:04:05.891
you should at least recognize my voice.

00:04:06.433 --> 00:04:08.894
If it's the chairman of Heaven Casino,
that's Chairman Do Hyeon-tae, right?

00:04:09.979 --> 00:04:12.648
- Who is this?
- Give Chairman Do this message.

00:04:13.399 --> 00:04:14.817
That his turn is next

00:04:14.900 --> 00:04:17.528
so he shouldn't do anything stupid
and just wait for his turn.

00:04:17.862 --> 00:04:19.238
KIM DAE-HO

00:04:22.241 --> 00:04:23.742
Weren't they supposed to be the best?

00:04:23.826 --> 00:04:25.703
- We'll find someone else.
- No!

00:04:26.495 --> 00:04:28.372
Are you crazy? Didn't you just hear that?

00:04:29.415 --> 00:04:30.749
He said to give me the message.

00:04:30.833 --> 00:04:33.961
He said to give the message
to Chairman Do Hyeon-tae of Heaven Hotel.

00:04:34.044 --> 00:04:36.922
They know exactly who I am,
and you want to hire someone else?

00:04:37.631 --> 00:04:39.300
Who knows what those scumbags will do?

00:04:39.383 --> 00:04:42.261
What if they tell Han Gyeong-wook
that Do Hyeon-tae is after the package?

00:04:42.803 --> 00:04:44.346
How are you going to fix it then?

00:04:44.430 --> 00:04:46.181
- I'm sorry.
- Darn it.

00:04:48.684 --> 00:04:52.521
Erase every trace of our conversations.

00:04:53.230 --> 00:04:57.026
I've never heard of or seen this hitman
or whatever he is. Understand?

00:04:58.736 --> 00:04:59.778
Yes, I understand.

00:05:02.823 --> 00:05:04.408
Chairman Do!

00:05:05.826 --> 00:05:07.912
Chairman Do!

00:05:07.995 --> 00:05:09.997
What in the world is going on?

00:05:10.080 --> 00:05:12.708
I mean, Hwang Hwa-san
is the new head of Heaven Capital?

00:05:12.791 --> 00:05:14.501
Has that old man
already shown up for work?

00:05:14.919 --> 00:05:15.920
What...

00:05:17.796 --> 00:05:19.089
You knew?

00:05:19.590 --> 00:05:22.927
How could this happen
the moment I had my nameplate made?

00:05:23.802 --> 00:05:25.596
Listen, you're not just

00:05:25.971 --> 00:05:28.390
going to stand by
and let this happen, are you?

00:05:29.099 --> 00:05:30.100
Hey.

00:05:31.393 --> 00:05:34.438
You think you're really a president
just because I call you one?

00:05:35.522 --> 00:05:37.358
- What?
- Mr. Geum.

00:05:37.858 --> 00:05:39.610
Your nameplate isn't what's at stake here.

00:05:40.819 --> 00:05:43.489
One wrong move and we're all dead.

00:05:44.031 --> 00:05:45.032
Get it?

00:05:45.366 --> 00:05:47.159
Listen carefully to what I'm about to say.

00:05:48.118 --> 00:05:49.286
If you want to live

00:05:50.204 --> 00:05:52.998
everything we've talked about
and everything we've done up until now...

00:05:54.166 --> 00:05:55.167
Forget it all.

00:05:56.335 --> 00:05:57.836
Just go back to being a lackey

00:05:58.587 --> 00:06:01.423
and be sure to lay low. Okay?

00:06:06.512 --> 00:06:07.513
But, Chairman, I...

00:06:10.599 --> 00:06:11.600
What...

00:06:24.363 --> 00:06:25.614
Is this it?

00:06:25.698 --> 00:06:26.699
That's right.

00:06:59.148 --> 00:07:00.149
Found it.

00:07:02.901 --> 00:07:04.820
Is this the package we were looking for?

00:07:04.903 --> 00:07:06.196
I'll have to check and see.

00:07:17.166 --> 00:07:19.543
Check the package on your own.
As for the torso...

00:07:20.794 --> 00:07:21.795
Give the torso to me.

00:07:22.713 --> 00:07:23.797
I already told you.

00:07:24.298 --> 00:07:25.549
I'll give it to you when the job's done.

00:07:28.260 --> 00:07:29.845
Hey, let's go. We're out of time.

00:07:31.263 --> 00:07:33.515
We have to finish off Han Gyeong-wook.

00:07:35.142 --> 00:07:36.143
Let's go.

00:07:53.535 --> 00:07:56.330
Once we open this,
there's no turning back.

00:07:56.955 --> 00:07:59.333
If anyone wants to back out, speak now.

00:07:59.792 --> 00:08:01.376
No hard feelings.

00:08:01.877 --> 00:08:03.378
There you go again,
trying to act all tough.

00:08:03.462 --> 00:08:05.464
We're not backing out
after all that we've been through.

00:08:05.547 --> 00:08:07.216
Isn't this our chance
to finish them all off?

00:08:07.800 --> 00:08:11.053
- I'm prepared.
- Let those punks come at us.

00:08:11.136 --> 00:08:13.680
We're running out of time.
Stop wasting it and open it.

00:08:47.965 --> 00:08:48.966
Huh?

00:08:50.342 --> 00:08:52.678
- It's locked.
- What did you think, you idiot?

00:08:53.178 --> 00:08:54.680
Well, unlock it then.

00:08:55.139 --> 00:08:57.933
Look, you clearly don't know
what you're talking about

00:08:58.016 --> 00:09:00.769
but if the file is encrypted,
it's hard to open.

00:09:01.645 --> 00:09:05.023
You can't open it with a setup this fancy?

00:09:05.107 --> 00:09:08.152
- Gosh, you're something else. Right?
- What do you mean he can't open it?

00:09:08.235 --> 00:09:10.154
Believe it or not,
our Gong-bok here is self-taught

00:09:10.237 --> 00:09:11.613
and has even hacked police CCTV feeds.

00:09:12.197 --> 00:09:13.615
Just wait a bit.
He can crack this in no time.

00:09:13.699 --> 00:09:15.617
Wait for what?

00:09:15.951 --> 00:09:17.244
I'll say this one more time.

00:09:17.327 --> 00:09:19.997
If you're trying to pull a fast one on me,
I won't let it slide.

00:09:20.414 --> 00:09:22.082
What the... You...

00:09:23.458 --> 00:09:26.003
Takes one to know one, right?
You think we're like you?

00:09:26.837 --> 00:09:29.006
- What about me?
- Are you asking because you don't know?

00:09:29.089 --> 00:09:31.300
You drugged the soup and stole my car!

00:09:31.383 --> 00:09:33.177
Was I in the wrong,
or were you just stupid?

00:09:33.260 --> 00:09:35.554
What? Stupid? Are you done talking?

00:09:35.637 --> 00:09:37.639
Hey, Ho-myeong.
Look at this shameless brat.

00:09:37.723 --> 00:09:39.850
How can we trust a scumbag like this
and keep working with him?

00:09:40.017 --> 00:09:41.768
Are you seriously barking right now?

00:09:41.852 --> 00:09:43.312
Hey, quiet down, will you?

00:09:45.647 --> 00:09:47.191
Gosh, you're so annoying.

00:09:47.482 --> 00:09:49.902
Hey, we shouldn't be
fighting amongst ourselves!

00:09:49.985 --> 00:09:51.320
Are you trying to get us all killed?

00:09:51.403 --> 00:09:52.487
He just keeps barking!

00:09:57.409 --> 00:09:59.453
Hey, Ma Gong-bok.
Can you crack this or not?

00:10:00.579 --> 00:10:03.624
I'll have to see,
but it'll probably take some time.

00:10:07.044 --> 00:10:09.129
Darn it. Something's not right.

00:10:09.880 --> 00:10:11.715
This file being encrypted means

00:10:11.798 --> 00:10:14.927
that our location could be exposed
when we access it.

00:10:15.385 --> 00:10:17.387
Exposed? To whom?

00:10:17.471 --> 00:10:18.680
It's too dangerous here.

00:10:18.764 --> 00:10:20.849
Pack up all this equipment.
Let's go somewhere safe.

00:10:35.113 --> 00:10:37.824
STORAGE-001
LOCATION ACQUIRED

00:10:51.713 --> 00:10:52.881
Comrade Major!

00:11:02.266 --> 00:11:04.935
We've picked up a signal from Storage 001.

00:11:05.185 --> 00:11:06.311
A signal?

00:11:06.728 --> 00:11:07.771
Where?

00:11:07.854 --> 00:11:10.399
Yeongseon Island in South Korea.

00:11:11.775 --> 00:11:12.818
Yeongseon Island...

00:11:21.368 --> 00:11:24.538
Looks like it's time
for a little trip down south.

00:11:28.583 --> 00:11:31.211
Hello to our viewers.
Welcome to Issue Prime.

00:11:31.295 --> 00:11:34.131
Today, we're joined
by candidate Han Gyeong-wook

00:11:34.214 --> 00:11:36.174
who holds a commanding lead in the polls

00:11:36.258 --> 00:11:38.176
in the election for mayor of Imcheon.

00:11:38.510 --> 00:11:40.387
- Welcome, Candidate Han.
- Yes, hello.

00:11:41.096 --> 00:11:43.223
I am Han Gyeong-wook,
candidate for mayor of Imcheon.

00:11:43.432 --> 00:11:46.226
Yes, your recent rise in the polls
has been quite remarkable.

00:11:46.310 --> 00:11:49.646
Some are even calling it a one-man race.

00:11:49.855 --> 00:11:50.856
However, some analysts suggest

00:11:50.939 --> 00:11:53.233
that if candidate Kim Seon-jung
hadn't withdrawn

00:11:53.650 --> 00:11:57.237
the current situation
wouldn't have been so easy to achieve.

00:11:57.571 --> 00:11:58.822
What are your thoughts on that?

00:11:59.698 --> 00:12:02.409
Well, I respect Candidate Kim's decision.

00:12:02.659 --> 00:12:03.744
However...

00:12:03.827 --> 00:12:07.581
I believe my poll numbers
aren't due to the absence of an opponent

00:12:07.664 --> 00:12:10.751
but are a result of
the public's expectations for my platform.

00:12:10.834 --> 00:12:12.044
Speaking of your platform

00:12:12.127 --> 00:12:14.004
I assume you're referring to the pledge
you made for this election

00:12:14.087 --> 00:12:17.424
which is the development
of the Yeongseon Island tourism complex.

00:12:17.966 --> 00:12:20.302
I'm curious about the reasoning
behind that proposal.

00:12:21.762 --> 00:12:23.638
The goal of the Yeongseon Island
development

00:12:23.722 --> 00:12:26.850
isn't to create some flashy tourist trap.

00:12:27.434 --> 00:12:30.395
It's about jump-starting
Imcheon's stagnant economy

00:12:30.479 --> 00:12:33.357
to improve the lives
of the Imcheon citizens.

00:12:34.107 --> 00:12:37.277
Higher incomes and job creation
for the Imcheon citizens.

00:12:37.361 --> 00:12:40.489
Those two things
are the core of my platform.

00:12:40.572 --> 00:12:43.867
But there's criticism that's been raised

00:12:43.950 --> 00:12:45.619
that this development
will lead to the ousting of residents.

00:12:45.702 --> 00:12:47.662
Do you have a plan to address this issue?

00:12:49.414 --> 00:12:50.916
As I've said

00:12:51.291 --> 00:12:54.294
the most important thing
is the lives of our citizens.

00:12:55.003 --> 00:12:56.755
I would be the first
to oppose any development

00:12:56.838 --> 00:12:58.131
that displaces our citizens.

00:12:58.382 --> 00:12:59.966
I will ensure that

00:13:00.050 --> 00:13:02.552
the profits go directly
back to the citizens of Yeongseon Island

00:13:02.636 --> 00:13:04.846
by putting
institutional measures in place.

00:13:05.222 --> 00:13:07.682
In four days, Candidate Han Gyeong-wook
will be on Yeongseon Island...

00:13:10.268 --> 00:13:14.898
That's our Assemblyman Han.
You're quite the smooth talker.

00:13:16.274 --> 00:13:17.275
You flatter me.

00:13:17.943 --> 00:13:20.112
Well, your election is in the bag.

00:13:20.195 --> 00:13:23.323
So, the project. How's that coming along?

00:13:24.241 --> 00:13:25.784
It's proceeding smoothly.

00:13:26.910 --> 00:13:29.037
Once the election polls turned in my favor

00:13:29.121 --> 00:13:31.289
the Mayor of Imcheon changed his tune.

00:13:31.998 --> 00:13:34.876
I recently got the approval
for the management and disposal plan

00:13:35.210 --> 00:13:37.212
which he had been stalling on.

00:13:37.838 --> 00:13:41.383
The remaining procedures
are basically just a formality.

00:13:42.634 --> 00:13:45.053
Most of the land
within the redevelopment zone

00:13:45.137 --> 00:13:47.222
has already been secured
by Heaven Capital.

00:13:47.305 --> 00:13:50.851
As for the residents holding out,
once demolition really begins

00:13:51.476 --> 00:13:52.644
they'll have no choice but to give in.

00:13:53.687 --> 00:13:57.315
It might not be that easy,
even with bulldozers.

00:13:58.108 --> 00:14:01.987
There are always cockroaches like that
wherever you go.

00:14:02.404 --> 00:14:05.198
You can try to get rid of them
over and over

00:14:05.282 --> 00:14:07.701
but they just keep crawling back out.

00:14:08.702 --> 00:14:12.414
Once I'm elected mayor,
the investors will move in right away.

00:14:12.497 --> 00:14:13.748
We have no time to delay.

00:14:14.708 --> 00:14:16.376
Whether we spray them with pesticide
or stomp them out

00:14:16.460 --> 00:14:18.044
they need to be exterminated quickly.

00:14:18.128 --> 00:14:20.505
We'll start clearing out Zone A.

00:14:20.589 --> 00:14:22.507
Once I win this election

00:14:22.591 --> 00:14:25.802
things will automatically pick up speed
in Zones B and C as well.

00:14:25.886 --> 00:14:30.724
Gosh, that's our Assemblyman Han.
Always so decisive, right?

00:14:32.350 --> 00:14:36.813
All right, just get through this election
without a hitch.

00:14:37.355 --> 00:14:42.444
After that, I'll make sure
to roll out the red carpet for you.

00:14:43.612 --> 00:14:44.613
Thank you.

00:14:50.827 --> 00:14:52.537
Assemblyman Han, one moment.

00:14:52.621 --> 00:14:53.705
Is it urgent?

00:14:54.164 --> 00:14:55.207
Yes.

00:14:56.625 --> 00:14:58.293
Go on and take care of it.

00:14:58.376 --> 00:15:01.713
I'll just relax here
and have some tea. Okay?

00:15:02.339 --> 00:15:04.758
- Then please excuse me for a moment.
- Yes, of course.

00:15:07.928 --> 00:15:08.929
What is it?

00:15:11.765 --> 00:15:12.974
We got a call from Ri Chol Jin.

00:15:14.309 --> 00:15:15.352
What?

00:15:15.435 --> 00:15:17.312
He says they detected a signal
trying to decrypt the package

00:15:17.395 --> 00:15:18.605
from Yeongseon Island.

00:15:20.649 --> 00:15:22.108
Jeong Ho-myeong.

00:15:22.400 --> 00:15:23.777
So it wasn't a bluff?

00:15:25.987 --> 00:15:28.281
- And Ri Chol Jin?
- He's on his way down now.

00:15:28.365 --> 00:15:29.366
Good.

00:15:30.951 --> 00:15:32.452
Contact our guys on Yeongseon Island.

00:15:33.203 --> 00:15:34.204
Tell all of them

00:15:34.955 --> 00:15:36.248
to gather here tomorrow.

00:15:36.331 --> 00:15:37.332
Yes, sir.

00:15:41.127 --> 00:15:43.088
Jeez, what kind of place is this?

00:15:48.635 --> 00:15:50.637
Gosh, this is crazy.

00:15:51.221 --> 00:15:54.224
You said this place was safe.
It's just a completely run-down resort.

00:15:57.769 --> 00:15:59.437
Aren't you supposed to be
South Korea's best agent?

00:15:59.521 --> 00:16:01.314
Shouldn't you have secured
a bomb shelter or something?

00:16:01.398 --> 00:16:02.774
Who has bomb shelters these days?

00:16:02.857 --> 00:16:05.110
This place is great.
Spacious and comfortable.

00:16:05.402 --> 00:16:08.029
There's a bathroom inside
and a place to sleep upstairs.

00:16:08.113 --> 00:16:09.823
The water's not working in the bathroom.
So what good is it?

00:16:10.407 --> 00:16:12.617
- The lights work, though.
- You're good at that kind of stuff.

00:16:13.493 --> 00:16:14.578
Go get the water running.

00:16:15.328 --> 00:16:17.122
Aren't you a good cook too? I'm hungry.

00:16:18.290 --> 00:16:20.292
All right, let's move.

00:16:23.587 --> 00:16:24.754
Are you trying to start a fight?

00:16:39.185 --> 00:16:40.895
Darn it. This is nuts.

00:16:45.442 --> 00:16:46.735
You don't inspire much confidence.

00:16:47.611 --> 00:16:50.405
I have no confidence in you.
Are you sure you can crack this?

00:16:52.115 --> 00:16:55.952
This encryption program was made
by the best minds in The Republic.

00:16:56.036 --> 00:16:58.955
Can some punk gangster really crack it?

00:16:59.039 --> 00:17:00.832
Darn it. There he goes again.

00:17:01.833 --> 00:17:03.627
Have a little faith.

00:17:03.710 --> 00:17:07.505
He's the most capable gangster I know.

00:17:09.257 --> 00:17:10.717
Mr. Jeong!

00:17:11.217 --> 00:17:12.594
A capable gangster?

00:17:14.554 --> 00:17:16.681
What's that supposed to mean?
That's a new one for me.

00:17:16.765 --> 00:17:18.558
If a guy is so capable,
why is he a gangster?

00:17:19.267 --> 00:17:22.812
Hey, you think the Hwasan Sect
is some third-rate gang?

00:17:22.896 --> 00:17:26.024
Then again, a spy like you
wouldn't know that, would you?

00:17:26.107 --> 00:17:28.818
There's no way you'd know about
noble values like chivalry and loyalty.

00:17:28.902 --> 00:17:30.278
I'm not a spy.

00:17:30.362 --> 00:17:32.822
I'm a special agent from
the Ministry of People's Armed Forces.

00:17:33.156 --> 00:17:36.451
I'm on a completely different level
from you lowlifes.

00:17:37.994 --> 00:17:39.663
But...

00:17:39.746 --> 00:17:41.081
there's something I'm curious about.

00:17:41.706 --> 00:17:44.626
Do you guys really want to go back
to your old lives that badly?

00:17:48.296 --> 00:17:49.381
Ma Gong-bok,

00:17:49.464 --> 00:17:52.967
you seem to have taught yourself
a lot about that program.

00:17:53.468 --> 00:17:54.636
Won't all that skill go to waste?

00:17:57.430 --> 00:17:58.973
And Gang Beom-ryong.

00:17:59.057 --> 00:18:01.267
You even got
the Friendly Convenience Store Award.

00:18:01.351 --> 00:18:03.561
You must have had some affection
for the store, right?

00:18:06.898 --> 00:18:10.443
Why would it be a waste?
It's all for the Hwasan Sect anyway.

00:18:10.527 --> 00:18:13.196
Once Hwasan Sect, always Hwasan Sect.
Isn't that right, Boss?

00:18:17.325 --> 00:18:18.368
Yes, that's right.

00:18:22.163 --> 00:18:23.790
And once you grab the diamonds

00:18:24.749 --> 00:18:26.459
you're just going to leave?

00:18:27.627 --> 00:18:29.546
The people you know on Yeongseon Island

00:18:30.255 --> 00:18:31.381
and your nephew.

00:18:31.881 --> 00:18:33.425
You don't mind never seeing them again?

00:18:35.385 --> 00:18:39.180
This is my last chance to fix the life
that was ruined ten years ago.

00:18:39.514 --> 00:18:42.016
You think I'd let some useless emotion
hold me back now?

00:18:42.100 --> 00:18:44.769
So you're just going to leave
without saying goodbye?

00:18:44.853 --> 00:18:47.772
If I drag things out with goodbyes
and get found out

00:18:48.148 --> 00:18:49.691
the Party will know I'm alive.

00:18:49.774 --> 00:18:51.818
You think they'll just leave me be?

00:18:52.569 --> 00:18:55.739
I'm Bulgae, a legend in the Republic's
Ministry of People's Armed Forces.

00:18:56.072 --> 00:18:58.616
Exceptional at martial arts,
a brilliant mind

00:18:58.700 --> 00:19:00.034
and perfect infiltration skills.

00:19:00.118 --> 00:19:02.829
You think they'd let
a talent like me go so easily?

00:19:02.912 --> 00:19:05.123
Gosh, I'm so sick of his bragging.

00:19:05.206 --> 00:19:07.959
But, Mr. Jeong, why do you ask?

00:19:08.042 --> 00:19:11.713
Once you clear your name,
you'll go back to the NIS, won't you?

00:19:14.340 --> 00:19:15.717
I can't go back.

00:19:16.634 --> 00:19:19.888
It's true I started all this
to get revenge on Han Gyeong-wook

00:19:19.971 --> 00:19:23.850
and reclaim my position
from ten years ago.

00:19:24.392 --> 00:19:25.977
Back then, that was
the most important thing to me.

00:19:26.895 --> 00:19:29.606
But I've had a realization recently.

00:19:31.524 --> 00:19:35.195
That protecting this Yeongseon Island

00:19:35.278 --> 00:19:37.155
where my family
and Oran Chinese Restaurant are

00:19:37.739 --> 00:19:39.282
is what's more important.

00:19:39.365 --> 00:19:41.534
Don't you feel like you're throwing away
ten years of suffering?

00:19:41.618 --> 00:19:43.787
Things are different now
than they were ten years ago.

00:19:43.870 --> 00:19:46.581
Now I have things to protect.

00:19:47.707 --> 00:19:50.335
An agent is going to be swayed
by petty emotions?

00:19:51.503 --> 00:19:55.089
Yes, maybe I am
being swayed by my emotions.

00:19:56.841 --> 00:20:00.220
But it's not as bad as you might think.

00:20:05.767 --> 00:20:07.477
You all should think carefully too.

00:20:07.560 --> 00:20:11.648
If going back to your old lives
is what you really want.

00:20:25.370 --> 00:20:27.914
JEONGSEOK BOARDING HOUSE

00:20:27.997 --> 00:20:29.749
I will ensure that

00:20:29.833 --> 00:20:32.252
the profits go directly
back to the citizens of Yeongseon Island

00:20:32.335 --> 00:20:34.754
by putting
institutional measures in place.

00:20:34.838 --> 00:20:36.172
In four days, Candidate Han Gyeong-wook

00:20:36.256 --> 00:20:37.799
will be on Yeongseon Island

00:20:37.882 --> 00:20:40.677
wrapping up his official campaign
with a large-scale rally.

00:20:42.804 --> 00:20:45.849
It looks like Han Gyeong-wook
is going to become mayor, right?

00:20:45.932 --> 00:20:47.016
I know, right?

00:20:47.100 --> 00:20:49.060
Just look at what a smooth talker he is.

00:20:49.143 --> 00:20:51.062
Anyone can see
he looks like the only person

00:20:51.145 --> 00:20:52.480
who can develop Yeongseon Island.

00:20:53.022 --> 00:20:56.901
But is it true that he and Ho-myeong
are mortal enemies?

00:20:57.610 --> 00:20:58.653
That's what he said.

00:20:59.988 --> 00:21:03.992
Then if he becomes mayor,
what's going to happen to our restaurant?

00:21:05.076 --> 00:21:08.454
He wouldn't just leave a restaurant
run by his enemy alone, would he?

00:21:12.083 --> 00:21:15.169
We'll have to figure something out.

00:21:15.420 --> 00:21:17.380
This is so frustrating.

00:21:17.881 --> 00:21:20.508
I thought we'd be back
at the restaurant in no time.

00:21:21.759 --> 00:21:25.013
Have you heard anything from Ho-myeong
about how things are going?

00:21:25.680 --> 00:21:28.558
I haven't contacted him on purpose.
I was afraid he'd worry.

00:21:29.100 --> 00:21:31.561
Hey! O-ran!

00:21:31.644 --> 00:21:32.896
We're in big trouble.

00:21:32.979 --> 00:21:34.272
- What?
- What is it?

00:21:34.355 --> 00:21:35.356
That...

00:21:56.377 --> 00:21:59.589
NOTICE OF EVICTION AND RELOCATION

00:22:00.465 --> 00:22:02.842
We all know you've been trying hard.

00:22:02.926 --> 00:22:04.552
But according to the news

00:22:04.636 --> 00:22:06.679
Han Gyeong-wook
is the top candidate for mayor.

00:22:06.763 --> 00:22:08.806
If he becomes mayor
and pushes through with his pledges

00:22:08.890 --> 00:22:11.851
all our homes will be torn down and
this development will be forced through.

00:22:11.935 --> 00:22:13.645
Come on, a protest?

00:22:13.853 --> 00:22:15.396
- You think that's going to stop it?
- Then...

00:22:15.897 --> 00:22:17.607
should we just sit back
and do nothing then?

00:22:18.024 --> 00:22:19.692
After everything they put us through.

00:22:19.776 --> 00:22:22.946
People who were tricked
by the free invitations from the casino

00:22:23.029 --> 00:22:26.491
business owners who were deceived
by offers of low-interest loans

00:22:26.574 --> 00:22:29.994
and people who were threatened
and blackmailed into selling their homes.

00:22:30.078 --> 00:22:34.207
We were all unjustly targeted
by Heaven Capital.

00:22:35.375 --> 00:22:37.752
We can't let them develop this area.

00:22:38.211 --> 00:22:42.215
We have to at least try to tell
the person who's going to be mayor.

00:22:42.298 --> 00:22:45.426
But he hasn't been elected yet

00:22:45.510 --> 00:22:47.387
so let's just wait a little longer.

00:22:48.346 --> 00:22:51.516
No, this isn't a situation
where we can just relax and wait.

00:22:51.599 --> 00:22:54.102
I rode my motorcycle all around
the neighborhood the other day.

00:22:54.185 --> 00:22:57.063
There are so many empty houses and shops.

00:22:57.313 --> 00:22:59.190
Seriously, the number has skyrocketed.

00:22:59.273 --> 00:23:00.358
Now that you mention it

00:23:00.441 --> 00:23:02.402
I saw it too the other day
when I was passing by.

00:23:03.194 --> 00:23:04.696
Around your restaurant

00:23:05.154 --> 00:23:08.574
- the shopping area was deserted.
- What?

00:23:09.242 --> 00:23:10.493
Around our restaurant too?

00:23:10.827 --> 00:23:12.328
Darn it!

00:23:12.787 --> 00:23:14.330
This development, or whatever it is...

00:23:14.414 --> 00:23:16.332
Are they trying to
kick all of us residents out?

00:23:16.416 --> 00:23:20.378
That's why we need to protest.
We have to make our intentions clear.

00:23:21.462 --> 00:23:24.298
Hey, trying to stop them
isn't going to solve anything.

00:23:25.133 --> 00:23:27.343
But what about your husband?
Still no word?

00:23:27.427 --> 00:23:30.013
You said he was looking for a way
to catch those guys.

00:23:40.440 --> 00:23:43.067
You were likely briefed
before you arrived.

00:23:43.151 --> 00:23:45.236
At this busy time,
with the Yeongseon Island Project underway

00:23:45.319 --> 00:23:48.322
there's a reason I've gone
out of my way to gather you all.

00:23:50.033 --> 00:23:54.203
It's to finally tie up the loose ends
from ten years ago.

00:23:54.287 --> 00:23:57.123
If they already tried to open the file

00:23:58.291 --> 00:24:00.084
is there any point in getting it back now?

00:24:00.168 --> 00:24:02.378
The transmission is encrypted.

00:24:02.920 --> 00:24:04.756
The package isn't easy to open.

00:24:05.506 --> 00:24:07.425
We still have
plenty of time to retrieve it.

00:24:24.567 --> 00:24:26.444
These are the ones who took the package.

00:24:27.487 --> 00:24:30.490
You might recognize some of these faces.

00:24:34.118 --> 00:24:36.621
Chairman Hwang Hwa-san
and Major Ri Chol Jin.

00:24:38.164 --> 00:24:40.958
You know them better than anyone

00:24:41.918 --> 00:24:43.294
so I'm counting on the two of you.

00:24:44.670 --> 00:24:46.297
Yes, understood.

00:24:47.840 --> 00:24:49.842
I'll get on it right away.

00:24:51.385 --> 00:24:55.181
We'll deploy the most elite agents from
the Ministry of People's Armed Forces.

00:24:55.640 --> 00:24:57.141
The job shouldn't be too difficult.

00:25:00.394 --> 00:25:01.771
- As for Chairman Do...
- Yes?

00:25:02.105 --> 00:25:04.607
You probably don't know much about them

00:25:04.690 --> 00:25:07.610
so let's have you
on rear support this time.

00:25:10.279 --> 00:25:11.531
No, sir.

00:25:11.614 --> 00:25:13.825
Actually, I've heard
quite a bit of information

00:25:13.908 --> 00:25:15.701
here and there to just be on support.

00:25:16.285 --> 00:25:18.037
By chance, of course.

00:25:18.538 --> 00:25:21.916
So what I'm saying is,
I think it would be for the best

00:25:22.083 --> 00:25:23.835
if I were to help out on the front lines.

00:25:34.762 --> 00:25:36.139
Chairman Do.

00:25:36.222 --> 00:25:39.892
Still can't shake off
your old gutter habits?

00:25:41.310 --> 00:25:42.311
What?

00:25:42.395 --> 00:25:44.355
You can't tell
what you should and shouldn't eat.

00:25:45.690 --> 00:25:47.275
What did you gobble up this time?

00:25:48.234 --> 00:25:50.403
I'm sure I made myself clear before.

00:25:51.737 --> 00:25:54.490
Stay out of it and wait.

00:26:00.538 --> 00:26:03.166
Oh, yes. You did say that.

00:26:03.416 --> 00:26:06.711
I was just trying to be helpful,
Deputy Director Han.

00:26:07.879 --> 00:26:10.214
I'm sorry. I'll keep that in mind.

00:26:11.465 --> 00:26:12.633
All of you, remember this.

00:26:13.968 --> 00:26:15.344
If this goes wrong

00:26:16.179 --> 00:26:17.763
we're all dead.

00:26:18.639 --> 00:26:22.810
If everyone just does their part properly

00:26:23.352 --> 00:26:25.980
we won't fail like we did ten years ago.

00:26:27.440 --> 00:26:29.650
This time, be sure
to retrieve the package.

00:26:30.151 --> 00:26:31.986
And as for the scumbags
involved in this...

00:26:33.362 --> 00:26:34.488
Get rid of them all.

00:26:43.623 --> 00:26:45.917
Did something bad happen in there, sir?

00:26:46.000 --> 00:26:47.585
Mr. Nam, you know what?

00:26:48.377 --> 00:26:50.880
We're about to be left high and dry.

00:26:51.964 --> 00:26:52.965
What?

00:26:53.466 --> 00:26:54.508
I mean, Deputy Director Han.

00:26:55.259 --> 00:26:59.055
He's dying to cut me out of this business.

00:26:59.680 --> 00:27:00.932
Shit!

00:27:01.015 --> 00:27:04.352
He even brought up my past
just to humiliate me.

00:27:04.435 --> 00:27:06.687
Do you think he's noticed our moves?

00:27:07.355 --> 00:27:08.898
No, I don't think so.

00:27:08.981 --> 00:27:11.108
If he knew,
he's not the type to stay quiet.

00:27:11.943 --> 00:27:15.279
It's just that
he's gotten all he can out of me

00:27:16.030 --> 00:27:18.574
and he has a spare
named Hwang Hwa-san ready

00:27:19.242 --> 00:27:20.826
so he's trying to get rid of me now.

00:27:21.369 --> 00:27:25.539
And that Hwang Hwa-san,
that sly fox has some gall.

00:27:25.748 --> 00:27:29.418
How could he even think of joining forces
with the man who sent him to prison?

00:27:29.502 --> 00:27:30.962
If it were me, I would never...

00:27:34.298 --> 00:27:35.341
What is it?

00:27:36.342 --> 00:27:37.385
If it were me?

00:27:39.387 --> 00:27:40.388
No.

00:27:41.264 --> 00:27:42.348
If it were you

00:27:43.474 --> 00:27:46.644
do you think it would be possible
to have a real friendship

00:27:47.270 --> 00:27:50.564
with the man who made you
rot in prison for ten years?

00:27:52.275 --> 00:27:54.068
- I doubt it would be.
- Right?

00:27:54.860 --> 00:27:58.447
Sure, he might have overlooked it
for the money

00:27:58.531 --> 00:28:02.159
but every now and then,
he'd feel a surge of anger.

00:28:03.452 --> 00:28:04.704
Out of revenge.

00:28:14.714 --> 00:28:17.300
Sir, if you're heading to Yeongseon Island

00:28:17.383 --> 00:28:18.592
why don't you ride with me?

00:28:18.968 --> 00:28:22.763
- It's fine.
- Oh, please. I insist.

00:28:22.847 --> 00:28:25.683
There's just something specific
I'd like to talk to you about.

00:28:26.183 --> 00:28:28.686
Okay? Please just ride with me this once.

00:28:34.734 --> 00:28:36.610
Tail those two.

00:28:36.944 --> 00:28:39.864
Where they're going
and what they're saying.

00:28:39.947 --> 00:28:42.533
Find out everything and report back to me.

00:28:43.117 --> 00:28:44.118
Yes, sir.

00:28:52.543 --> 00:28:55.755
Comrade Major,
we found Bulgae's residence.

00:28:55.838 --> 00:28:57.214
You did?

00:28:58.466 --> 00:29:00.968
That reactionary scumbag
who betrayed the Republic.

00:29:02.094 --> 00:29:04.972
I'm curious what luxuries he was enjoying.

00:29:17.360 --> 00:29:20.863
A ride in a nice car
and an extravagant meal on top of it.

00:29:22.198 --> 00:29:25.534
What you want to talk about
must be pretty serious.

00:29:26.077 --> 00:29:27.495
Well...

00:29:27.578 --> 00:29:31.665
It could be difficult,
or it could be simple.

00:29:31.749 --> 00:29:34.585
I just thought,
as coworkers in the same boat

00:29:34.668 --> 00:29:37.463
we could discuss
the nature of our business.

00:29:37.546 --> 00:29:39.090
- That's why I invited you here.
- I see.

00:29:39.799 --> 00:29:42.802
The nature of our business, you say.

00:29:44.261 --> 00:29:46.514
You received the same offer,
didn't you, sir?

00:29:47.723 --> 00:29:50.810
That they'd give you a share
if you joined the Yeongseon project.

00:29:50.893 --> 00:29:55.398
Look, I'm a little hesitant to say this
because I'm worried it'll come out wrong.

00:29:56.232 --> 00:29:58.526
"Giving us the share"
is a nice way of putting it.

00:29:58.609 --> 00:29:59.860
In reality, the core of it

00:30:00.861 --> 00:30:03.572
is a setup where
Han Gyeong-wook takes everything.

00:30:04.240 --> 00:30:07.701
I mean, in the end,
we're the ones doing all the dirty work

00:30:07.785 --> 00:30:10.788
and Deputy Director Han is the one
who monopolizes all the profit.

00:30:11.914 --> 00:30:15.084
So, this is what I'm trying to say. I...

00:30:15.418 --> 00:30:17.002
And I thought this was going to be
something else.

00:30:19.463 --> 00:30:23.759
You have a real knack for making
simple things sound complicated.

00:30:25.052 --> 00:30:26.095
Pardon?

00:30:26.178 --> 00:30:30.474
So you're saying
we should cut out Deputy Director Han

00:30:31.267 --> 00:30:33.227
and take over this project,
isn't that right?

00:30:35.020 --> 00:30:37.022
Impressive.

00:30:37.731 --> 00:30:41.569
Chairman, your reaction is so enthusiastic

00:30:42.862 --> 00:30:44.029
that I'm a little taken aback.

00:30:47.241 --> 00:30:48.993
It's a golden opportunity
to take over the business

00:30:49.076 --> 00:30:50.870
and get my revenge.

00:30:50.953 --> 00:30:53.914
So, what's the point
of beating around the bush?

00:30:55.916 --> 00:31:00.296
So, what do you need me to do?

00:31:05.009 --> 00:31:06.010
Hey, Ho-myeong.

00:31:06.635 --> 00:31:09.597
Hey, we've got a big problem over here.

00:31:09.680 --> 00:31:12.558
I think the victims of Heaven Capital
are about to rise up.

00:31:12.641 --> 00:31:13.809
Rise up about what?

00:31:13.893 --> 00:31:16.770
I heard Han Gyeong-wook's election
is a sure thing.

00:31:16.854 --> 00:31:19.023
They're saying if he pushes ahead
with his campaign pledges

00:31:19.106 --> 00:31:22.651
they're all going to be driven out,
so things are really tense right now.

00:31:22.735 --> 00:31:26.238
In three days, on the day Han comes
to Yeongseon Island for a campaign rally

00:31:26.322 --> 00:31:29.241
everyone is dead set on holding a protest.

00:31:29.325 --> 00:31:33.120
You know well that Han Gyeong-wook
and those Capital guys are in it together.

00:31:33.871 --> 00:31:35.164
You think they're just
going to let that happen?

00:31:35.247 --> 00:31:37.166
I know. But how are the residents
supposed to believe

00:31:37.249 --> 00:31:39.585
that Han Gyeong-wook
and those thugs are in cahoots

00:31:39.668 --> 00:31:41.795
when there's no proof?

00:31:41.879 --> 00:31:45.174
They all feel their homes and stores
were unfairly taken

00:31:45.257 --> 00:31:46.884
and that the development has to stop

00:31:47.259 --> 00:31:49.053
so they just want to make
their voices heard.

00:31:50.888 --> 00:31:52.181
Got it.

00:31:52.264 --> 00:31:53.682
Don't worry too much

00:31:53.766 --> 00:31:55.893
and just make sure
you don't get involved. All right?

00:31:56.685 --> 00:31:58.729
- I'll call you back.
- Wait, Ho-myeong.

00:31:58.812 --> 00:31:59.813
Yes?

00:32:02.441 --> 00:32:04.151
Lately, Ji-woo...

00:32:05.402 --> 00:32:06.779
When he wakes up from his sleep

00:32:07.446 --> 00:32:09.490
he cries and asks for you.

00:32:10.991 --> 00:32:11.992
He does?

00:32:12.076 --> 00:32:14.537
I think it's because
his dad suddenly isn't around

00:32:14.620 --> 00:32:16.288
and his environment has changed.

00:32:16.622 --> 00:32:17.957
He seems anxious.

00:32:19.208 --> 00:32:21.418
It's been a long time
since Ji-woo has seen you.

00:32:27.007 --> 00:32:30.553
Okay. Please tell Ji-woo
that Daddy will definitely come see him.

00:32:32.388 --> 00:32:33.389
Okay.

00:32:52.241 --> 00:32:53.325
How is it going?

00:32:53.409 --> 00:32:55.244
I'm running it with the program
I got from the dark web

00:32:55.327 --> 00:32:57.037
but honestly,
I have no idea how long it'll take.

00:32:57.121 --> 00:32:58.122
It's almost done.

00:32:59.248 --> 00:33:00.541
It's 2%.

00:33:01.292 --> 00:33:03.127
Hey, it's running right now.
Just wait a bit.

00:33:03.419 --> 00:33:06.171
We don't have time.
If you don't think it'll work, say so now.

00:33:06.422 --> 00:33:09.174
- So we can find another way.
- What is it? Why the sudden rush?

00:33:10.509 --> 00:33:13.387
In three days, at Han Gyeong-wook's
campaign rally on Yeongseon Island

00:33:13.470 --> 00:33:15.723
the victims of Heaven Capital
are going to hold a protest.

00:33:15.806 --> 00:33:16.807
A protest?

00:33:17.850 --> 00:33:19.143
Then Nam-il will...

00:33:19.518 --> 00:33:21.687
Well, probably. He lost his house too.

00:33:22.062 --> 00:33:24.982
If that protest happens,
Han Gyeong-wook won't just stand by.

00:33:25.065 --> 00:33:27.651
He'll try to stop it somehow,
even if he has to involve the Capital.

00:33:27.735 --> 00:33:30.154
Wait a minute. Then we shouldn't be
sitting around like this.

00:33:30.237 --> 00:33:33.198
Right. That's the first smart thing
you've said.

00:33:33.282 --> 00:33:34.575
How long are we going to be stuck on this

00:33:34.658 --> 00:33:36.577
when we don't even know
when it'll be cracked?

00:33:36.660 --> 00:33:40.331
Wouldn't it be better to just go now
and smash the Heaven Capital guys?

00:33:40.414 --> 00:33:42.750
- Let's go.
- Let's think this through.

00:33:43.208 --> 00:33:44.501
Damn it.

00:33:44.585 --> 00:33:45.836
All you do is think.

00:33:49.340 --> 00:33:51.800
How about putting that on silent
at crucial moments?

00:33:52.134 --> 00:33:53.802
I was expecting a call
from the convenience store headquarters

00:33:53.886 --> 00:33:55.054
and it slipped my mind.

00:33:56.221 --> 00:33:57.514
That ringtone... Darn.

00:34:00.726 --> 00:34:03.228
Beom-ryong, I'm out of prison.

00:34:03.646 --> 00:34:04.688
Let's meet now.

00:34:05.773 --> 00:34:06.774
What is it?

00:34:08.192 --> 00:34:09.443
What did they say at headquarters?

00:34:10.027 --> 00:34:11.445
Hey, don't touch it.

00:34:12.696 --> 00:34:14.239
Gosh, seriously...

00:34:14.740 --> 00:34:16.158
It's Chairman Hwang.

00:34:18.452 --> 00:34:19.620
What?

00:34:21.330 --> 00:34:22.623
He got out of prison.

00:34:23.624 --> 00:34:26.794
Hwang Hwa-san is out, now of all times?

00:34:51.610 --> 00:34:53.028
Boss!

00:34:57.449 --> 00:34:59.535
The distribution business
you guys were running

00:35:02.037 --> 00:35:03.414
was a convenience store?

00:35:04.665 --> 00:35:06.333
I'm sorry for not telling you.

00:35:08.043 --> 00:35:09.795
You've all been through a lot.

00:35:10.963 --> 00:35:13.549
From now on, only good things

00:35:14.591 --> 00:35:15.718
are in store for you.

00:35:21.181 --> 00:35:22.182
What?

00:35:22.266 --> 00:35:26.186
So are you saying
you're the new head of Heaven Capital?

00:35:27.229 --> 00:35:30.357
Yes. To make Deputy Director Han
let his guard down

00:35:30.441 --> 00:35:33.152
I had to accept the position.

00:35:33.235 --> 00:35:35.904
But still, how could you work
under Deputy Director Han?

00:35:35.988 --> 00:35:39.032
I'm not the only one
who's done something drastic.

00:35:39.116 --> 00:35:43.412
You teamed up with that punk from the NIS,
your sworn enemy, to get revenge.

00:35:43.495 --> 00:35:45.289
You're no different, are you?

00:35:46.874 --> 00:35:48.709
You knew everything?

00:35:50.544 --> 00:35:52.004
Listen.

00:35:52.421 --> 00:35:56.717
I can read you guys like a book.

00:35:58.594 --> 00:35:59.803
Beom-ryong, you.

00:35:59.887 --> 00:36:02.055
I knew something was wrong
from the look on your face

00:36:02.139 --> 00:36:03.182
when you came to visit.

00:36:04.349 --> 00:36:07.770
To get revenge on Han Gyeong-wook
and rebuild the Hwasan Sect

00:36:07.853 --> 00:36:09.480
I'm also willing to do whatever it takes.

00:36:11.148 --> 00:36:12.357
Boss.

00:36:14.193 --> 00:36:16.820
Han Gyeong-wook
has completely let his guard down.

00:36:17.654 --> 00:36:21.992
Whether we seize this opportunity or not

00:36:23.035 --> 00:36:25.871
is up to you two.

00:36:27.915 --> 00:36:30.167
Yes, just tell us what to do.

00:36:35.214 --> 00:36:37.049
The package that disappeared
ten years ago.

00:36:37.341 --> 00:36:39.009
You two have it, right?

00:36:47.100 --> 00:36:50.771
Bring me that package.

00:36:56.485 --> 00:36:58.946
They'll discuss it
and then bring the package?

00:36:59.613 --> 00:37:01.782
As soon as they're done
talking with the NIS agent

00:37:02.533 --> 00:37:04.076
they promised to contact me.

00:37:04.660 --> 00:37:05.661
Okay.

00:37:06.662 --> 00:37:07.913
But...

00:37:08.789 --> 00:37:12.084
Doesn't it feel a little off to you?

00:37:12.751 --> 00:37:14.378
What do you mean?

00:37:14.461 --> 00:37:18.715
I've been burned by him before, so I know.
That NIS agent is no joke.

00:37:18.799 --> 00:37:20.592
He might have already caught on

00:37:20.676 --> 00:37:22.803
that we're trying
to intercept the package.

00:37:26.723 --> 00:37:27.724
Ah, by any chance...

00:37:28.392 --> 00:37:32.312
Your guys aren't going to flip
and side with him, are they?

00:37:32.396 --> 00:37:33.814
You don't have to worry.

00:37:35.148 --> 00:37:37.109
Beom-ryong and Gong-bok

00:37:38.068 --> 00:37:40.112
will soon be in touch.

00:37:41.196 --> 00:37:42.197
Okay.

00:37:42.906 --> 00:37:44.575
Well, that's a relief then.

00:37:48.412 --> 00:37:51.790
So, you want us to join forces
with your boss?

00:37:52.040 --> 00:37:53.125
Yes.

00:37:54.293 --> 00:37:55.586
It's hard to believe, I know.

00:37:56.086 --> 00:37:58.881
But our boss has been waiting
for a chance to get revenge

00:37:58.964 --> 00:38:00.257
right under Han Gyeong-wook's nose.

00:38:00.340 --> 00:38:03.385
If we just bring him the package,
everything will fall right into place.

00:38:03.468 --> 00:38:06.013
- And you think that makes sense?
- Why doesn't it make sense?

00:38:06.096 --> 00:38:09.182
Don't we and the boss have the same goal?
To get revenge on Han Gyeong-wook.

00:38:12.978 --> 00:38:17.649
But how can we trust that your boss
will actually go through with the revenge?

00:38:17.733 --> 00:38:20.527
He rotted in prison for ten years.
Of course he wants revenge.

00:38:20.611 --> 00:38:21.945
Isn't that right, Beom-ryong?

00:38:30.746 --> 00:38:34.207
At least this guy's
got his head on straight.

00:38:37.461 --> 00:38:38.879
Yes, that's right.

00:38:39.171 --> 00:38:41.965
The boss is not the type
to take something lying down.

00:38:42.049 --> 00:38:43.050
Right?

00:38:44.134 --> 00:38:45.302
Well, not exactly.

00:38:45.385 --> 00:38:47.220
The moment he teamed up
with Han Gyeong-wook to get out

00:38:47.304 --> 00:38:49.139
he was thinking more about
the bottom line than revenge.

00:38:51.099 --> 00:38:53.977
Okay, let's just say
that he really is out for revenge.

00:38:54.436 --> 00:38:55.646
But has Hwang Hwa-san said

00:38:55.729 --> 00:38:57.856
what he's going to do
with the Yeongseon Island project

00:38:57.940 --> 00:38:58.982
after getting his revenge?

00:39:03.987 --> 00:39:07.199
If he pushes ahead
with the Yeongseon Island project

00:39:07.282 --> 00:39:08.575
as the CEO of Heaven Capital

00:39:08.992 --> 00:39:12.329
then what's the difference between
Hwang Hwa-san and Han Gyeong-wook?

00:39:12.871 --> 00:39:14.873
Or Han Gyeong-wook and Hwang Hwa-san?

00:39:16.541 --> 00:39:19.252
How dare you compare someone
like Han Gyeong-wook to our boss?

00:39:20.087 --> 00:39:21.088
Our boss is...

00:39:26.259 --> 00:39:27.302
Our boss is...

00:39:31.640 --> 00:39:34.768
What about your boss?
Why did you trail off?

00:39:35.310 --> 00:39:37.145
You know full well,
so stop pretending you don't.

00:39:37.229 --> 00:39:40.440
Hwang Hwa-san is planning
to take this project for himself.

00:39:40.524 --> 00:39:43.485
What do you think you know about our boss,
running your mouth off like that?

00:39:43.568 --> 00:39:46.530
Mr. Jeong, you've got it all wrong.
Our boss isn't like that.

00:39:46.613 --> 00:39:47.864
What if what Bulgae says is true?

00:39:49.324 --> 00:39:52.619
Even so, are you still going to do
what Hwang Hwa-san says?

00:40:04.881 --> 00:40:06.883
Right, to go back to the Hwasan Sect.

00:40:06.967 --> 00:40:09.177
Sure, that's what you've wanted
for the past ten years.

00:40:09.970 --> 00:40:10.971
But is it...

00:40:11.722 --> 00:40:14.224
worth trampling over innocent people for?

00:40:14.307 --> 00:40:16.852
What's the point of asking?
Thugs will be thugs.

00:40:17.352 --> 00:40:19.563
When it's about them getting rich
and living easy

00:40:19.646 --> 00:40:23.108
do you think they even care
what happens to other people?

00:40:26.528 --> 00:40:28.321
You think I like doing this?

00:40:28.405 --> 00:40:31.742
I've been family with the boss
for 30 years. But...

00:40:31.825 --> 00:40:33.952
To just go up to the boss now and say,
"Hey! You're in the wrong!"

00:40:34.828 --> 00:40:37.539
Do you think it's as easy as it sounds
to go against him like that?

00:40:38.915 --> 00:40:40.625
What do you want me to do?

00:40:40.959 --> 00:40:43.462
You want me to stab my boss
in the back after all this time?

00:40:48.759 --> 00:40:50.635
Is that the only reason you're hesitating?

00:40:52.095 --> 00:40:54.598
Is it really because
of your loyalty to your boss?

00:40:55.307 --> 00:40:58.351
Or is it because you want to right a wrong
but you don't have the courage?

00:41:04.191 --> 00:41:05.317
Gang Beom-ryong.

00:41:07.027 --> 00:41:08.862
Didn't you want to start fresh?

00:41:41.728 --> 00:41:42.729
You guys.

00:41:44.773 --> 00:41:46.191
Go back to the convenience store.

00:41:47.109 --> 00:41:50.320
If that's all the commitment you've got,
you won't accomplish anything anyway.

00:41:53.323 --> 00:41:54.574
Go back to the convenience store.

00:41:54.658 --> 00:41:56.701
And stay quiet there
until this whole thing is over.

00:41:57.494 --> 00:41:59.788
Bulgae and I will finish this ourselves.

00:42:00.247 --> 00:42:01.248
The two of us?

00:42:06.294 --> 00:42:07.504
If that's really how you feel

00:42:08.964 --> 00:42:10.841
- I'll step aside.
- Boss!

00:42:12.509 --> 00:42:14.010
I'm sorry.

00:42:14.094 --> 00:42:15.679
For being so indecisive.

00:42:15.929 --> 00:42:18.473
What do you mean you're stepping aside?
Just because of what he said?

00:42:20.517 --> 00:42:21.518
Boss!

00:42:23.311 --> 00:42:24.729
Hey, Gang Beom-ryong!

00:42:27.858 --> 00:42:28.859
Boss.

00:42:29.484 --> 00:42:31.486
How can you just leave like this?

00:42:31.570 --> 00:42:32.696
Please.

00:42:32.779 --> 00:42:34.990
Are you going to betray
the chairman now? Is that it?

00:42:38.243 --> 00:42:39.327
Seriously...

00:42:40.120 --> 00:42:42.038
Then what am I supposed to do?

00:42:45.083 --> 00:42:46.376
I'm sorry. I just...

00:42:47.836 --> 00:42:49.880
I don't know what to do anymore either.

00:42:52.257 --> 00:42:55.260
Boss. What makes you think I'd know?

00:42:56.803 --> 00:43:00.098
Just tell me what to do.
I'll do whatever you say.

00:43:02.058 --> 00:43:03.977
I'm sorry. Let's talk later.

00:43:04.978 --> 00:43:07.147
Later when? When?

00:43:08.231 --> 00:43:09.232
Boss!

00:43:16.156 --> 00:43:18.533
A South Korean citizen, Bong Je-sun.

00:43:19.159 --> 00:43:21.620
He did a good job
of hiding out and living here.

00:43:22.370 --> 00:43:25.665
He's been peddling a false story
to everyone that he has amnesia.

00:43:27.709 --> 00:43:32.172
He's been completely corrupted
by those South Korean puppet dramas.

00:43:32.547 --> 00:43:36.426
And these South Korean fools
actually fell for that?

00:43:36.509 --> 00:43:38.929
It seems having a family
helped him avoid suspicion.

00:43:39.346 --> 00:43:40.430
A family?

00:43:48.939 --> 00:43:50.232
Where's Bulgae now?

00:43:50.315 --> 00:43:53.318
After he was hospitalized
for a car accident recently

00:43:53.401 --> 00:43:55.237
his trail suddenly went cold.

00:43:57.322 --> 00:44:00.158
So he's gone into hiding?

00:44:00.242 --> 00:44:01.243
Yes.

00:44:02.077 --> 00:44:03.286
What's your plan, sir?

00:44:03.370 --> 00:44:05.622
If Bulgae is determined to stay hidden

00:44:06.414 --> 00:44:08.875
even our agents
will have a hard time finding him.

00:44:11.211 --> 00:44:15.048
Look at this punk smiling so brightly.
Doesn't suit him at all.

00:44:15.131 --> 00:44:17.509
- Sir?
- Aren't you curious?

00:44:17.592 --> 00:44:19.803
Just how far gone Bulgae is.

00:44:22.722 --> 00:44:25.725
Let's make him
come crawling back to us on his own.

00:44:37.988 --> 00:44:39.531
Have you just been sitting here
this whole time?

00:44:41.199 --> 00:44:42.409
What do you mean?

00:44:42.492 --> 00:44:45.287
You know what I mean.
You're waiting for those thugs.

00:44:46.705 --> 00:44:48.331
Did they really have to storm out

00:44:48.415 --> 00:44:50.208
just because you said a few things
they didn't like?

00:44:50.292 --> 00:44:52.127
It's not like you were wrong.

00:44:56.881 --> 00:44:58.591
But seriously, are you going to be okay?

00:45:01.052 --> 00:45:02.304
I mean, I'm fine.

00:45:03.138 --> 00:45:06.808
This isn't the first mess I've been in
since my days as an agent

00:45:07.517 --> 00:45:09.144
so I can just feel it.

00:45:10.562 --> 00:45:12.772
- This whole situation is just...
- What about it?

00:45:12.856 --> 00:45:14.482
Let's be honest.
Nothing about this is good.

00:45:15.400 --> 00:45:18.862
We went through all that trouble
to find the package but can't open it.

00:45:18.945 --> 00:45:21.781
And over there, with the protests and all,
things are just getting more tangled.

00:45:28.246 --> 00:45:30.957
So what are you trying to say?

00:45:31.875 --> 00:45:35.837
Before this whole thing gets any worse
and we're in too deep to get out

00:45:36.963 --> 00:45:38.506
you should look after your family

00:45:39.215 --> 00:45:40.508
and I'll take the diamonds.

00:45:40.592 --> 00:45:43.428
We should each find a way
to save ourselves.

00:45:44.721 --> 00:45:47.223
- What?
- What if those thugs

00:45:48.350 --> 00:45:49.976
decide to side with the other guys?

00:45:50.685 --> 00:45:54.105
What if they side with their boss
and come after us?

00:45:55.315 --> 00:45:57.067
You think the two of us can handle that?

00:45:57.150 --> 00:46:00.403
So you're saying we should give up
on Han Gyeong-wook and run away?

00:46:00.487 --> 00:46:02.238
If Han Gyeong-wook gets elected

00:46:02.322 --> 00:46:04.199
don't you know it's all over
for Yeongseon Island?

00:46:04.282 --> 00:46:07.118
Fine, you're right.
If Han Gyeong-wook gets elected

00:46:07.202 --> 00:46:10.455
and takes over Yeongseon Island,
this whole island is doomed.

00:46:11.539 --> 00:46:13.333
But what if your family gets hurt
before that happens?

00:46:15.293 --> 00:46:17.712
We have a slim chance
even if we all fight together.

00:46:17.796 --> 00:46:20.382
And now it looks like
even those thugs are about to turn on us.

00:46:21.800 --> 00:46:24.427
I'm just saying we need to
think about this rationally.

00:46:24.511 --> 00:46:27.013
Whether this is actually possible or not.

00:46:37.690 --> 00:46:39.984
HEO NAM-IL

00:46:50.453 --> 00:46:51.996
The number you have dialed is unavailable.

00:46:53.206 --> 00:46:54.874
This is so weird.

00:46:55.834 --> 00:46:57.293
This has never happened before.

00:46:59.254 --> 00:47:00.547
Doesn't something feel off to you?

00:47:02.006 --> 00:47:04.509
I mean, we haven't heard from him
since he left with those men.

00:47:05.927 --> 00:47:08.513
You don't think they got him in debt
and dragged him off somewhere, do you?

00:47:08.596 --> 00:47:09.848
Honestly, the things you imagine.

00:47:10.640 --> 00:47:12.392
Do you think Manager Bong
is anything like you, Nam-il?

00:47:14.602 --> 00:47:16.396
Hey, I'm just saying it
because I'm worried.

00:47:17.230 --> 00:47:20.024
Lately he's always been injured
whenever he comes back from somewhere.

00:47:20.108 --> 00:47:21.943
And whose fault do you think that is?

00:47:23.194 --> 00:47:26.281
He'll call when he calls.
Just help me make these protest signs.

00:47:26.364 --> 00:47:28.533
I'm doing all the work here,
including your share!

00:47:32.162 --> 00:47:33.913
- I'm getting a call.
- Pick up.

00:47:34.706 --> 00:47:35.790
Uncle? What's up?

00:47:35.874 --> 00:47:37.417
Is this Heo Nam-il's phone?

00:47:40.462 --> 00:47:41.463
Yes, speaking. Who is this?

00:47:41.546 --> 00:47:43.715
I'm from the gas company.

00:47:43.798 --> 00:47:46.885
We got a report about a gas smell,
so I came to check

00:47:46.968 --> 00:47:48.303
but no one's home.

00:47:48.970 --> 00:47:51.055
What? A gas smell?

00:47:51.139 --> 00:47:52.140
Yes.

00:47:52.223 --> 00:47:55.101
It seems like
there's a gas leak in your house.

00:47:55.185 --> 00:47:56.853
I think you need to come and check it out.

00:47:56.936 --> 00:47:58.855
Okay, yes. I'm on my way.

00:48:01.399 --> 00:48:02.942
- I have to step out for a minute.
- Where are you going?

00:48:03.026 --> 00:48:04.611
Home. Apparently,
there's a gas leak at my house.

00:48:04.694 --> 00:48:06.362
You're going home? At a time like this?

00:48:06.446 --> 00:48:09.199
What if the gas explodes
and my house blows up?

00:48:09.282 --> 00:48:11.576
What's the point of protesting
to get my house back then?

00:48:12.368 --> 00:48:13.703
I'll be right back.

00:48:14.037 --> 00:48:16.581
So could you please work
on my signs for me, okay?

00:48:16.915 --> 00:48:17.957
- But...
- Make it a good one.

00:48:18.041 --> 00:48:19.292
Hey, wait...

00:48:22.086 --> 00:48:23.087
Seriously?

00:48:34.432 --> 00:48:37.018
Fine, you're right.
If Han Gyeong-wook gets elected

00:48:37.101 --> 00:48:38.686
and takes over Yeongseon Island

00:48:39.938 --> 00:48:41.481
this whole island is doomed.

00:48:42.607 --> 00:48:44.484
But what if your family gets hurt
before that happens?

00:48:51.074 --> 00:48:52.158
Stop right there!

00:48:56.746 --> 00:48:58.039
Oh, come on!

00:49:10.677 --> 00:49:11.678
Dad!

00:49:16.349 --> 00:49:17.976
Daddy will help you.

00:49:18.059 --> 00:49:19.519
- Really?
- Yes.

00:49:19.602 --> 00:49:21.771
But Daddy, have you done this before?

00:49:21.854 --> 00:49:24.440
Of course. This is all I did
when I was a kid.

00:49:25.650 --> 00:49:27.026
- Daddy.
- Yes?

00:49:27.110 --> 00:49:28.945
That's not right.

00:49:29.028 --> 00:49:31.155
- Why?
- Here.

00:49:31.239 --> 00:49:33.283
You need to make it spacious here

00:49:33.616 --> 00:49:35.410
so he has a place to live.

00:49:37.036 --> 00:49:39.372
Why would Masked Racer live inside?

00:49:39.455 --> 00:49:41.916
He should be outside,
guarding the house like this.

00:49:42.625 --> 00:49:43.918
No.

00:49:44.002 --> 00:49:46.921
He'll get bored
if he's outside all by himself.

00:49:47.005 --> 00:49:49.007
But if he's in the house

00:49:49.090 --> 00:49:52.427
he can play with Mommy,
Daddy, and Grandpa.

00:49:53.052 --> 00:49:55.179
That's why he has to live in the house.

00:50:00.351 --> 00:50:01.894
- Daddy.
- Yes?

00:50:02.645 --> 00:50:04.772
When do I get to go home?

00:50:05.356 --> 00:50:09.444
I want to go home now.
It's so boring here.

00:50:22.624 --> 00:50:24.125
- Ji-woo.
- Yes?

00:50:24.709 --> 00:50:27.211
As soon as I'm done with work

00:50:27.295 --> 00:50:29.964
I'll take you straight home, Ji-woo.

00:50:30.381 --> 00:50:32.383
Once we're home, we'll have fun

00:50:32.467 --> 00:50:34.927
with Mommy, Daddy, and Grandpa
every single day.

00:50:35.637 --> 00:50:38.348
- Really?
- Of course. I promise.

00:50:38.431 --> 00:50:39.557
Just wait a little bit longer.

00:50:41.559 --> 00:50:44.145
We'll have to build a big house. Right?

00:50:44.228 --> 00:50:49.275
With Grandpa, Mom, and Dad here...
Mr. Kim is here too. Right?

00:50:49.359 --> 00:50:51.235
We'll have to build it much bigger.

00:50:51.319 --> 00:50:53.321
- Okay.
- Yes, like this...

00:50:53.404 --> 00:50:58.284
Look! Masked Racer
is going to dive right in.

00:51:29.982 --> 00:51:31.192
We're closed.

00:51:34.821 --> 00:51:35.822
Oh, really?

00:51:40.952 --> 00:51:43.621
I saw that the lights were on
as I was passing by.

00:51:44.330 --> 00:51:46.040
So I thought you were open.

00:51:47.959 --> 00:51:50.294
Do you need something?

00:51:51.546 --> 00:51:52.547
Not really, but...

00:51:53.506 --> 00:51:57.301
I was on my patrol
and I guess I'm getting a little hungry.

00:51:59.554 --> 00:52:01.347
Do you have any lunch boxes left?

00:52:09.397 --> 00:52:12.024
We're in the middle of closing,
so all we have are cup noodles.

00:52:13.985 --> 00:52:15.236
That's fine.

00:52:25.163 --> 00:52:26.622
About the convenience store...

00:52:29.000 --> 00:52:31.169
Did you decide to close down?

00:52:31.252 --> 00:52:32.378
Yes.

00:52:32.795 --> 00:52:34.714
I had to for personal reasons.

00:52:36.507 --> 00:52:39.010
Isn't it a shame?
After all your hard work.

00:52:40.011 --> 00:52:42.930
I heard it's hard to be chosen
as a Friendly Convenience Store.

00:52:43.014 --> 00:52:46.309
I just got lucky, that's all.

00:52:51.105 --> 00:52:54.817
Do you really have to
close down the store?

00:52:55.318 --> 00:52:56.569
I mean, you know

00:52:56.652 --> 00:52:59.655
that there are over
ten convenience stores around here.

00:53:00.490 --> 00:53:04.744
But me and the other officers on patrol,
we all only come here.

00:53:05.620 --> 00:53:07.747
Your store is the friendliest.

00:53:10.792 --> 00:53:11.793
Friendly.

00:53:14.462 --> 00:53:18.674
That was just me forcing a smile,
afraid that my sales would drop.

00:53:19.550 --> 00:53:21.928
I told you before, didn't I?
I used to be a thug.

00:53:22.637 --> 00:53:24.096
You might not know this, Mi-kyung

00:53:24.806 --> 00:53:27.558
but ten years ago, I was running around
doing all sorts of bad things.

00:53:28.351 --> 00:53:30.853
Like "the Hwasan Sect's iron fist"
or their "Problem Solver."

00:53:30.937 --> 00:53:33.981
When people hyped me up like that,
it all went to my head

00:53:35.066 --> 00:53:36.818
and I did plenty of things
I shouldn't have.

00:53:38.486 --> 00:53:39.987
You've got me all wrong.

00:53:40.988 --> 00:53:43.032
I'm not a friendly guy like that.

00:53:47.203 --> 00:53:50.915
Then what's your definition
of a friendly person?

00:53:53.835 --> 00:53:55.670
Whatever it is, I'm not it.

00:53:56.420 --> 00:53:58.005
That's how I've lived for so long.

00:54:05.763 --> 00:54:06.806
You know...

00:54:09.350 --> 00:54:11.227
When you work at a police station

00:54:12.019 --> 00:54:14.397
there are always regulars who show up.

00:54:15.106 --> 00:54:17.608
Whether for being drunk and disorderly
or for assault.

00:54:17.692 --> 00:54:22.530
And those kinds of bad habits
are really hard to break.

00:54:23.281 --> 00:54:24.991
But out of a hundred of those people

00:54:25.074 --> 00:54:28.244
there's always that one person
who suddenly stops showing up.

00:54:29.287 --> 00:54:31.372
From what I've seen of you so far

00:54:33.583 --> 00:54:34.917
out of those hundred people

00:54:36.294 --> 00:54:37.378
I think you're

00:54:38.754 --> 00:54:40.298
that one person.

00:55:12.830 --> 00:55:15.416
RESTRICTED NUMBER

00:55:23.049 --> 00:55:24.634
Did you get the photo?

00:55:24.717 --> 00:55:26.260
Comrade Major.

00:55:26.552 --> 00:55:28.971
Our Bulgae,
taking in and raising a nephew.

00:55:29.305 --> 00:55:31.432
I saw it with my own eyes,
and I still couldn't believe it.

00:55:32.350 --> 00:55:35.102
Weren't you always the type
to just live for your own amusement?

00:55:35.186 --> 00:55:37.563
Don't you dare touch
a single hair on Nam-il.

00:55:37.647 --> 00:55:39.482
Don't get worked up.

00:55:39.565 --> 00:55:41.233
I haven't done anything yet.

00:55:42.735 --> 00:55:44.779
But you know full well, don't you?

00:55:45.446 --> 00:55:48.366
That what happens next
depends entirely on you.

00:55:48.616 --> 00:55:49.659
What do you want?

00:55:50.743 --> 00:55:52.912
Do you want me to come back to the Party?

00:55:52.995 --> 00:55:55.081
Well, that's a given.

00:55:55.539 --> 00:55:57.083
You have the package, don't you?

00:55:57.750 --> 00:56:01.545
Sneak it away from the guys you're with
and bring it to me.

00:56:01.629 --> 00:56:03.339
All I have to do is hand over the package?

00:56:03.422 --> 00:56:07.426
Right. If you hand over the package,
I won't lay a finger on your nephew.

00:56:07.635 --> 00:56:10.262
But I can't give you a lot of time.

00:56:11.138 --> 00:56:13.349
If you want your nephew to be safe

00:56:14.308 --> 00:56:15.476
decide quickly.

00:56:55.433 --> 00:56:59.228
Comrade Major, are you really going to
let that punk live?

00:57:00.187 --> 00:57:01.772
Won't that cause problems for us later?

00:57:01.856 --> 00:57:03.983
What are you talking about?

00:57:04.066 --> 00:57:05.568
As soon as we get the package

00:57:05.651 --> 00:57:08.863
we'll get rid of both
Bulgae and his nephew.

00:57:09.321 --> 00:57:11.240
We're getting rid
of Comrade Bulgae as well?

00:57:13.159 --> 00:57:14.910
He's someone who betrayed the Party once.

00:57:15.327 --> 00:57:16.746
What makes you think
he wouldn't do it again?

00:57:18.289 --> 00:57:20.791
He must be summarily executed
according to the laws of the Republic.

00:57:23.169 --> 00:57:24.170
Comrade Major.

00:57:47.443 --> 00:57:48.944
It's been ten years, hasn't it?

00:57:49.028 --> 00:57:50.279
Is Nam-il okay?

00:57:55.201 --> 00:57:56.243
Can't you tell by looking?

00:57:57.203 --> 00:58:01.332
Man, it's been ten years
since we've seen each other

00:58:01.415 --> 00:58:04.376
and you still have no manners
when it comes to your master.

00:58:04.710 --> 00:58:07.296
Fine, whatever. No need to drag this out.

00:58:08.380 --> 00:58:09.548
The package?

00:58:27.316 --> 00:58:28.526
I kept my promise.

00:58:29.568 --> 00:58:31.153
Now let my nephew go.

00:58:33.489 --> 00:58:34.824
You've really changed.

00:58:36.325 --> 00:58:38.953
Falling for such an obvious ploy.

00:58:39.036 --> 00:58:40.412
You've changed too, Comrade Major.

00:58:42.498 --> 00:58:43.791
No matter how bad things got,

00:58:43.874 --> 00:58:46.127
you weren't someone
who'd stoop to telling such pathetic lies.

00:58:47.920 --> 00:58:50.673
I have to make up for my mistake
from ten years ago, don't I?

00:58:52.758 --> 00:58:54.426
The reactionary scumbag, Bulgae

00:58:54.885 --> 00:58:57.972
will be summarily executed
according to the laws of the Republic.

00:59:01.600 --> 00:59:04.603
Are you so sure that's the real package?

00:59:05.521 --> 00:59:06.772
What?

00:59:06.856 --> 00:59:07.857
What if...

00:59:09.608 --> 00:59:11.527
I brought you a fake?

00:59:13.154 --> 00:59:14.405
Why, you...

00:59:15.447 --> 00:59:17.700
It seems that living in South Korea

00:59:18.200 --> 00:59:20.327
has taught you a few tricks.

00:59:20.411 --> 00:59:22.997
Weren't you the one
who was trying to trick me first?

00:59:24.540 --> 00:59:25.875
All right then, let's do this.

00:59:26.709 --> 00:59:30.004
My original plan
was to just kill you both.

00:59:31.046 --> 00:59:32.756
But for now, I'll just keep you alive

00:59:32.840 --> 00:59:35.885
and torture you
until you tell me where the package is.

00:59:53.527 --> 00:59:55.529
Your footwork is still as fancy as ever.

00:59:56.530 --> 01:00:00.034
But no matter how quick you are,
do you think you can take on all of us?

01:01:07.935 --> 01:01:09.311
You...

01:01:09.395 --> 01:01:11.230
Who said I came alone?

01:01:16.360 --> 01:01:17.361
What are you doing?

01:01:32.001 --> 01:01:35.170
Nam-il is captured by a man
named Comrade Major Ri Chol Jin.

01:01:36.463 --> 01:01:38.340
He could be killed
if I don't bring the package.

01:01:38.424 --> 01:01:39.425
So?

01:01:40.384 --> 01:01:42.011
You're just going to
hand over the package?

01:01:49.018 --> 01:01:50.269
Can't you tell it's a trap?

01:01:52.187 --> 01:01:55.357
Will this Ri Chol Jin let you live?

01:01:55.441 --> 01:01:56.442
Didn't you hear me?

01:01:58.652 --> 01:02:01.113
I said Nam-il could be killed.

01:02:01.196 --> 01:02:02.823
If I have to, I'll go by myself

01:02:02.906 --> 01:02:05.701
lure them out with this package,
and rescue Nam-il.

01:02:06.285 --> 01:02:08.704
Weren't you just saying
you'd forget your nephew and leave?

01:02:08.787 --> 01:02:10.414
You said you were
going to look out for yourself.

01:02:11.498 --> 01:02:12.499
That was...

01:02:15.586 --> 01:02:16.587
Anyway...

01:02:17.504 --> 01:02:19.214
I'm taking this package.

01:02:22.593 --> 01:02:25.429
Geez. You think you can do that alone?

01:02:28.807 --> 01:02:30.059
I'll go with you.

01:02:31.977 --> 01:02:36.732
Let's secure both the package
and your nephew.

01:02:39.485 --> 01:02:40.527
The two of us?

01:02:42.654 --> 01:02:44.365
Ri Chol Jin is not some pushover.

01:02:45.574 --> 01:02:48.452
He must have brought
the Republic's most elite agents.

01:02:48.535 --> 01:02:50.996
So? Is there a problem?

01:02:51.080 --> 01:02:52.081
What?

01:02:52.164 --> 01:02:53.374
You said it yourself

01:02:53.457 --> 01:02:55.959
that you're the top agent in
the Ministry of People's Armed Forces.

01:02:56.043 --> 01:02:58.379
We have the best agents
from both the North and the South here.

01:02:58.462 --> 01:02:59.963
There's nothing we can't do.

01:03:02.174 --> 01:03:04.718
I heard you were
North Korea's elite agents

01:03:04.802 --> 01:03:05.969
so I was a little nervous.

01:03:07.012 --> 01:03:08.263
But you're nothing special.

01:03:09.473 --> 01:03:10.933
What would you have done
if I hadn't shown up?

01:03:11.016 --> 01:03:13.310
I told you I'd be fine alone.
Go rest some more.

01:03:14.144 --> 01:03:16.522
So the sworn enemies are joining forces?

01:03:17.189 --> 01:03:19.149
You think that's going to change anything?

01:03:19.233 --> 01:03:21.568
Why? I think things are already changing.

01:03:21.652 --> 01:03:22.736
Can't you see?

01:03:24.863 --> 01:03:29.034
Should I tell you a bit
about what's going to happen next?

01:03:29.118 --> 01:03:32.162
The spy punks who dared to set foot
on Yeongseon Island

01:03:32.246 --> 01:03:33.831
will be brutally crushed.

01:03:34.540 --> 01:03:36.959
After that, the pissed-off Han Gyeong-wook

01:03:37.042 --> 01:03:39.753
will probably send other spies
or his underlings, right?

01:03:41.088 --> 01:03:42.840
But do you think they can stop us?

01:03:44.466 --> 01:03:47.094
It'll just mean
more casualties on your side.

01:03:51.181 --> 01:03:52.724
Go tell Han Gyeong-wook

01:03:53.684 --> 01:03:55.519
to get ready to pay for his crimes.

01:04:18.709 --> 01:04:19.960
Nam-il, are you okay?

01:04:20.043 --> 01:04:22.254
Tell him he doesn't need to
worry about me anymore.

01:04:22.337 --> 01:04:25.048
So the great Bulgae's being swayed.

01:04:25.132 --> 01:04:26.925
- I'm back.
- Boss!

01:04:27.009 --> 01:04:29.386
I have to stop our boss
from taking the wrong path.

01:04:29.470 --> 01:04:31.513
- What do we do first?
- We're going to catch Han Gyeong-wook.

01:04:31.597 --> 01:04:33.765
I've already called for backup to help us.

01:04:33.849 --> 01:04:35.058
Have you been well, Je-sun?

01:04:35.142 --> 01:04:36.185
A difficult request?

01:04:36.268 --> 01:04:37.686
- You should stop right now.
- Stop what?

01:04:37.811 --> 01:04:38.812
Having feelings for me.

01:04:38.896 --> 01:04:41.023
What do you think the success rate
of this operation is?

01:04:41.106 --> 01:04:42.941
- About 50%?
- You think that's even possible?

01:04:43.025 --> 01:04:45.486
If we use the package as bait,
it's totally possible.

01:04:45.569 --> 01:04:47.571
- I'll see you there.
- Stop it, no matter what.

01:04:47.654 --> 01:04:48.739
Do you understand me?

01:04:48.822 --> 01:04:50.657
Hand over the package and back off.

01:04:50.741 --> 01:04:51.950
And if I refuse?

01:04:52.034 --> 01:04:53.869
Let's go back to that day ten years ago.

01:04:53.952 --> 01:04:56.830
What happens if Prosecutor Gang
doesn't make it in time?

01:04:56.914 --> 01:04:58.373
Gong-bok!

01:05:00.167 --> 01:05:01.293
Hand over the package!

01:05:01.376 --> 01:05:02.961
We're only halfway through life.

01:05:03.045 --> 01:05:04.922
We'll have to fight
like our lives depend on it.